Algorithm:
1.	Start
2.	Input: Read the integer value n (number for which factorial is to be calculated).
3.	Define the recursive function factorial(n):
o	If n == 0 or n == 1, return 1 (Base case).
o	Else, return n * factorial(n-1) (Recursive case).
4.	Call the recursive function to calculate factorial(n).
5.	Output: Display the result of factorial(n).
6.	End
Pseudocode:

Start
    Input n
    Function factorial(n):
        If n == 0 or n == 1 then
            Return 1
        Else
            Return n * factorial(n - 1)
    End Function
    
    result = factorial(n)
    Output result
End
